On May 18 , the Ministry of Finance promulgated the " Measures on the Administration of Supplementary Funds for Special Awards for Structural Adjustment of Industrial Enterprises " , which will arrange special awards to promote the elimination of excess capacity in the coal and iron and steel industries , with a total amount of 100 billion yuan .
Recently , several local governments , such as Shanghai , Shanxi , Shandong , Jiangsu and Heilongjiang , have put forward some suggestions on how to defuse excess capacity .
Among them , many provinces have even suggested that the central government should actively seek financial support for their provinces to go to capacity .
One example is that coal-to-capacity targets , announced in just eight provinces , stand at 90 % of the nation's plans to cut coal production .
In an interview with reporters , Lin Boqiang , director of the China Energy Policy Research Institute of Xiamen University , said that the " go-to capacity " of the steel and coal industries is far from enough to rely on 100 billion yuan from the central government , and more funds need local governments and enterprises to solve the problem . How to solve the problem ?
Shanxi Province recently announced the implementation rules of coal production capacity to reorganize Shanxi Coking Coal Group into a state-owned capital investment company , reorganization and integration of the assets and operations of enterprises , and the construction of a brand-new business model .
The actual shortfall could be three times as large as the subsidy , said Yin Yumin , minister of the Ministry of Human Resources and Social Security , adding that the initial statistics on " capacity-to-capacity " were 1.3 million people in the coal system and 500,000 in the steel system .
