The activities not only received the support of all the cadres and staff of the District Tobacco Bureau , but also attracted retired cadres and family members of the staff and workers to participate in the environmental protection practice . The three generations of old and young people worked together to protect the forest , clean up the garbage and contribute their part to the construction of the " beautiful South Yue " .
This volunteer activity aims to protect the landscape resources of Nanyue and promote the concept of " caring for others , caring for society and caring for nature " . It also enables the next generation to receive education from childhood and pass on the virtues of voluntary service .
It is reported that since its establishment in early April this year , the " 636 " voluntary service brigade has developed 16 members , and has carried out a series of voluntary service activities such as visiting disabled retail customers , helping tobacco farmers to care for tobacco leaves , Ya'an earthquake love donation and so on , thus becoming a volunteer force that conveys positive energy by heart .
