The International Symposium on New Energy Development and Technology , jointly organized by the State Grid Corporation and the International Electrician Commission , was held in Frankfurt , Germany .
At present , it has become a global trend to accelerate the development of new energy and promote the clean and low-carbon transformation of energy .
As for the large-scale development and utilization of new energy , there are many problems and challenges , such as system security , long-distance transportation and technology economy , which need to be faced and solved .
Shu Yan Biao , chairman of the State Grid Corporation , revealed that the State Grid Corporation is planning to expand the size of the synchronous grid , strengthen the existing regional grid interconnection , and increase the cross-area transmission capacity to about 350 million kilowatts by 2020 .
It is reported that Chongqing currently has 18 shale gas exploration rights established by the Ministry of Land and Resources and the first shale gas mining right in China--China Petrochemical Fuling shale gas field .
By January 2017 , the city of Chongqing had drilled 368 shale gas wells ( excluding parameter wells ) and put into production 261 . Recently , with the good news that four shale gas exploration wells in the south of Pingqiao area of Nanchuan , Sinopec , China , are producing more than 200,000 cubic meters a day , the world's first commercial shale gas field outside North America is expected to build 10 billion cubic meters of production capacity this year in accordance with the plan .
It is understood that 10 billion cubic meters of shale gas field is equivalent to a 10 million-ton large oil field .
It is understood that shale gas , as a clean energy source , can reduce carbon dioxide emissions by 12 million tons a year after the completion of the 10 billion square shale gas field .
