The announcement by China Development and Reform Commission officials on the early completion of the 11th Five-Year emission reduction targets has given the steel industry , which has been suppressed by limited electricity production , a strong expectation of a resumption of production .
Although the steel mills have not received a clear notice from the local government that the work on energy conservation and emission reduction is over , the industry estimates that around December 15 , 2010 , steel mills , which were originally limited in production , will continue to resume production , and steel prices may start to come under pressure .
No notice of the end of the power limit has been received , but in fact the pressure on companies has been much less than September and October , a private steel company in Hebei province told reporters .
Some parts of Hebei have repeatedly issued power-limited production documents , and at one time adopted a forced pull-off method to restrict the production of enterprises .
Reporters learned from the local enterprises that at present most of Hebei's steel mills have resumed work , limited production pressure relief .
Zhang Tieshan , an analyst with my steel network , predicts that the terminal demand for construction steel will gradually shift from strong to weak because the north is already in winter .
In addition to the gradual end of energy saving and emission reduction , by December 15 , most of the steel mills will basically resume production , and the products will reach the local market before New Year's Day .
The increase in the supply of resources will put some pressure on the price of steel , which is currently on the rise .
Big energy companies are all " rich countries " , so which of the world's many energy companies take the most advantage of the money ?
Exxon Mobil , the US oil and gas producer , topped the list of the top 50 listed energy companies in 2011 with a market capitalisation of $ 406.3 billion , followed by PetroChina and Royal Dutch Shell , the famous PFC energy company said yesterday .
In the PFC list , PetroChina won twice in 2007 and 2009 , with Exxon Mobil at the top of all other years .
In the list of the top 50 in 2011 , three companies from mainland China were shortlisted , in addition to PetroChina , No . 2 , and Sinopec , No . 9 , and China Offshore Oil , No . 15 .
But while oil prices are far higher than they were four years ago , the CEO of PFC Energy points out that there are a number of reasons for the overall low market capitalisation , including a decline in North American gas prices and a low level of activity in the global stock market , according to PFC .
