American Media : Scientists at the Air Force Engineering University of China study laser satellites for the removal of space waste
Chinese scientists have come up with a bold and innovative proposal to use large lasers to clean up cluttered Earth orbits , destroy old satellites and their sky garbage , US media said on Monday .
Researchers at China Air Force Engineering University wrote a paper on how space debris can be irradiated into smaller , less damaging pieces by using a space-based platform laser , according to a study entitled " Sky-based Laser Removal of Small-Scale Space Fragments Variable Track Model " .
Space waste has been a concern of international space agencies for years , and NASA has considered a variety of options to track , detect and remove man-made debris , the report said .
The ways to remove large-scale space debris include giant nets used to clean up and collect waste , as well as magnets that can be used to suck them out of orbit . Chinese scientists conducted laser simulations and concluded that this would be an effective way to clean up the Earth's orbit .
" ( Simulation study ) provides a necessary theoretical basis for the application of space debris removal technology in space-based platform , " the paper said .
A 2014 study by Lockheed Martin , the US defence giant , found that there are about 200 threats a day for satellites in orbit .
High-speed debris moving along the Earth's orbit is seen as a serious threat to future space missions , described by experts at the European Space Agency as a " deadly chain of threats " . High-speed debris has continued to increase over the past year .
Space is basically empty , but the space next to the Earth is becoming more crowded , and each satellite we send into space will eventually become another piece of debris orbiting the Earth , and over time the debris will pile up .
The more debris , the more likely a satellite that is still functioning is to be hit by debris , thereby damaging or destroying a multimillion-dollar investment .
All space agencies have drawn up plans to clean up space waste in the future , the report said .
NASA is considering using jet gas to reduce the speed of debris and get it out of orbit . Europe is considering launching a satellite carrying a large net to capture debris and bring it back to Earth . Japan's idea is to capture debris with an electric chain .
For now , China has also come up with a solution to space waste , using a large laser to smash floating space waste into less harmful debris .
The installation of such a laser on a satellite would be effective enough to clean up space , at least according to simulation results , according to a paper published by a group of researchers at China Air Force Engineering University in the German journal Optics .
The only way to prove its effectiveness is to test it , and there are no plans for such a mission , but perhaps sooner or later someone will install a laser on a satellite and send it into space , the report said .
Once done , we can finally begin to eliminate the problem of space rubbish once and for all .
( Compile / Hu Jing , Wang Hai Fang )
Xi Jinping's Mystery of Strictly Governing the Party in an All-round Way
On January 11 , at the second plenary meeting of the 19th Central Commission for Discipline Inspection of the Communist Party of China ( CPC ) , General Secretary Xi Jinping delivered an important speech , stressing that " the persistence on the road will lead the Party to an all-round and strict administration of the Party and create a new situation of all-round and strict administration of the Party " .
On the comprehensive strict rule of the Party , General Secretary Xi Jinping has a lot of images of the metaphor , together review !
" Tigers " should be beaten openly , and " flies " should be fluttered , and the Party should be promoted to extend to the grass-roots level in an all-round way , and the problem of corruption that occurs around the masses should be severely remedied .
--On January 11 , 2018 , Xi Jinping delivered an important speech at the Second Plenary Session of the 19th Central Discipline Inspection Committee of the Communist Party of China
In order to ensure that the power given by the Party and the people is not abused , and that the sharp sword of punishing evil and good will never be exposed to dust , the vast number of cadres in charge of discipline inspection and supervision should be loyal , conscientious , abide by discipline and law , and be clean and honest , so as to ensure that the power given by the Party and the people is not misused .
--On January 11 , 2018 , Xi Jinping delivered an important speech at the Second Plenary Session of the 19th Central Discipline Inspection Committee of the Communist Party of China
Grasp the implementation must not come into full swing , just shout slogans , do not act can not , the meeting alone , the issuance of documents is not enough , must fall to the ground .
