A picture to understand : Bitcoin's legal status around the world
Absrtact : In addition to the natural price correction triggered by speculative attributes , the collapse of the digital currency has nothing to do with the " old enemy " -regulatory risk .
From the visual map , the Eastern countries have a more conservative attitude towards Bitcoin than the West , and the world's dominant countries are still watching the legitimacy of the digital currency , representing the " Black Swan risk " is still very large .
* This article is from Wall Street News , editor Wang Mu . For more information , please visit Wallstreetcn . com , or download Wall Street to see APP . *
Bitcoin prices fell below $ 10,000 on Tuesday , their biggest one-day drop in three years , following a spate of regulatory turmoil in major markets such as China , South Korea and the European Union , where the global digital currency , led by Bitcoin , has been bloodied this week .
In addition to the natural price correction triggered by speculative attributes , the collapse of the digital currency has also been linked to the long-standing " old enemy " -regulatory risk .
At this important juncture , Howard Much . net , a visual large data website , produced a map showing the legitimacy and degree of regulation of Bitcoin in countries around the world .
As shown below , green represents the legitimate market for Bitcoin ; orange represents the neutral market , although it has not yet publicly legalized Bitcoin status , but there are no major restrictions on its use ; pale pink represents the restricted market , where local governments try to use digital money through red-line policy or regulation ; deep pink represents Bitcoin is defined as an illegal country ; and grey is a country that has not yet commented .
( Pictured above from the Howard Much . Net Visualization Team on January 15 )
The paper points out that the distribution of non-green color blocks in the picture shows that the traditional oriental countries have a more conservative attitude towards Bitcoin than in the West .
Russia is the largest country that currently defines Bitcoin as illegal , China is one of the biggest restricted markets for Bitcoin , and India is one of the biggest countries that has yet to comment on Bitcoin and has yet to introduce policies .
North America and Western Europe are the regions with the highest acceptance of Bitcoin , that is , the distribution of green blocks is more concentrated .
In the Middle East and Latin America , there is a marked divergence of views on Bitcoin , and the distribution of color blocks in the above-mentioned areas is more mixed .
Among them , Iraq , Iran , Turkey and Brazil are legitimate Bitcoin markets , Afghanistan , Pakistan , Saudi Arabia , Egypt and Bolivia have some restrictions on their trading and use , and more Latin American countries have not yet spoken about Bitcoin .
Taken together , the data show that 99 of the 246 countries surveyed worldwide ( or 40 % ) do not impose restrictions on the trading and use of Bitcoin , i . e . , green and orange areas .
Seven countries ( or 3 % ) are restricted markets ( pale pink ) , 10 countries ( or 4 % ) define Bitcoin as illegal ( deep pink ) , and 130 countries ( or 53 % ) have yet to deal more with digital currency information ( gray ) .
This suggests that countries , which account for 53 % of the world's main body ( more than half ) , are still waiting to see the legitimacy of the digital currency , led by Bitcoin , and that the " black swan risk " of Bitcoin is still large , as some of them may eventually make legislative decisions to limit digital money .
The article argues that global regulators have not yet fully understood the emerging category of digital money , and may be the main reason why most countries have not yet made a statement .
Although the " popularity " of Bitcoin has grown exponentially since last year , it does not mean that all countries are interested , some countries may be concerned about the threat of local currency , or more about the use of digital currency by criminal organizations .
Wall Street has written a detailed summary of international regulatory news on Bitcoin since last week , including China's efforts to crack down on the OTC's centralized service online platform and mobile App , while South Korea is still considering shutting down the digital currency exchange , which the European Union believes has not been widely accepted and warned investors about the risk of " losing their blood " .
From any point of view of regulation , acceptance / criticism and adoption , 2018 will be the year of the global central bank's digital currency .
Russia and other big countries criticized the legitimacy of the Bitcoin , in fact , to give way to the official issue of digital currency .
The BBC calls Beijing the most exciting city : making foreigners feel like " living in a new era "
Beijing may have a long history of 3,000 years , but it is also rapidly becoming today's modern glamour city , according to British media .
The Chinese capital , with its surprisingly high-speed Internet , sophisticated technologies such as face-recognition software , has invested heavily in artificial intelligence and unrivalled international energy , making it one of the most exciting cities for exploratory foreigners .
" If I can succeed there , I can succeed anywhere in the future , " said German expatriate Clemens Seth , who quoted singer Frank Sinatra as praising the lyrics of New York City .
" If Sinatra lived to this day , he would probably sing about cities like Beijing , " said Seth , creative director at Traveler's Archives . " Living in this city will make you feel like you're living in a new era and will always be able to keep up with the trend , " he said .
" People generally have a sense of being at the center of something grandiose , it's hard to say , but it keeps a lot of foreigners there for a long time , " Simon Norton , who recently lives in Beijing , wrote on his personal blog site 4 Corners7 Seas . " They want to see what it's going to be , and they want to see it with their own eyes . "
The city's high-quality , high-speed Internet and technology-friendly environment make daily life easier than ever before , the report said .
" Beijing is rapidly transforming into a cash-free society , with the Internet integrating the functions of traditional wallets into smartphones , making it easier for everyone to do a lot of deals , " said Andy Penia Fulert , now deputy editor-in-chief of the Beijing Children's Web site in Manila .
But smartphones are just the beginning of Beijing's technological ambitions , and facial recognition software has become so popular that many mobile phone applications use it to make bank transfers and payments , get people into apartments and offices , and even use it to verify the identity of online car drivers , the report said .
Beijing also recently announced plans to spend Rmb13.8 billion to build an artificial intelligence science park , where more than 400 companies will settle , focusing on the development of artificial intelligence technologies ranging from biometric to autopilot .
Food is also at the heart of many major festivals in China over the years . Participation in these celebrations is highly regarded by foreigners , and the Spring Festival is one of the most important social and economic festivals and one of the easiest festivals for foreigners to take part in .
" I suggest helping Chinese friends prepare for the New Year and clean their apartments as well as the red Spring Festival couplets with New Year's greetings posted on their homes . On New Year's Eve , all family members gather together to have a big meal and then stay up until midnight to greet the New Year with loud fireworks . For foreigners , spending the night with friends and family is really an opportunity to blend in , " he said .
The number of foreigners in Beijing is large and growing , but the language barrier in China and the convenience of communication among expatriates are easy to justify their incomplete integration into local culture , the report said .
" Some foreigners have been living in China for many years but have little experience with their host country , " he said . " If your initial attempt to reach out to the Chinese is not successful , it's easy to feel more comfortable with other foreigners . "
In these so-called " foreign bubbles " , foreigners mingle only among foreigners and do not touch local and local cultures . Foreigners huddle in their own communities , eat in Western restaurants , and only foreigners among their friends .
The easiest way to overcome this is to learn a little Mandarin-easier than one might think .
" An hour or two a week of Chinese private lessons or an entry-level radio play should fit everyone's busy schedule , " he said .
Learning even a few classic short sentences can be helpful in shopping , ordering meals in a restaurant or chatting in a taxi .
The report says stubborn air pollution is also a fact of everyday life , but in recent years the government has tried to contain some problems .
Residents stress that it is important to go outdoors in warmer months where pollution is often lighter , using blue sky days as an opportunity to wander through historic alleys or explore popular Ritan parks .
" Beijing is the Chinese city that can find the most things below the surface , " Norton said . " You can find great artistic and musical activities , indulgent nightlife , historical wonders , ultra-modern business districts and ancient Hutongs . "
Will China lag behind if it does not build this type of warship ?
With the recent announcement of plans by the world's major naval powers to build new frigates , it seems that the frigate has become the focus of the naval attention of the major powers overnight . First , Japan decided to purchase two new frigates in its 2018 defense budget , which led to a substantial breakthrough in Japan's DEX frigate plan , followed by the recent announcement by US Lockheed Martin of the latest U . S . FG frigate plan .
With the launch of the latest Type 054A frigate at the end of 2017 , it marks the construction of as many as 29 of the 54A frigates , approaching the total of the 53H series of frigates , and since the launch of the first 054A in 2006 , the 54A has been built for 12 years , even around the world , with the number of such high-performance frigates built in the United States , with the exception of Perry in the 1980s .
And the reason for the construction of so many 054A is simple , that is affordable , easy to use , plus years of naval arrears .
054A frigate has been favored by the Chinese navy for many years because of its high cost-effective and good combat effectiveness . Its 4000 - ton displacement , carrying a 76 - millimetre main gun , 32 - unit sea red flag-16 and fish-8 anti-submarine missile launching system , 8 eagles strike 83 and a straight-9 helicopter , although it was built in 2006 , and the design time of the ship is very early in the world .
But this is , after all , a ship designed at the beginning of the 21st century , with weapons on one side , and its power systems and electronic radar equipment already far behind the world's mainstream frigate , such as Europe's same type of frigate already equipped with full-power propulsion , small multi-functional phased array radar , large-size helicopter deck , the time has come to develop a new model .
So how China's new frigate should develop is directly related to its future positioning and the strategic policy of our Chinese navy .
The future development of the Chinese navy is bound to become a blue-water navy , and the future is bound to go to the ocean . With the rapid deployment and display of force in areas closely related to China's vital interests , it is necessary to have a strong fighting capacity to ensure that China's vital interests in the region will not be damaged , so it appears that the new Hu Wei River will develop towards a large-scale and ocean-going development .
Looking at the positioning of the new frigate in the future Chinese naval sequence , the future Chinese navy should be similar to that of the U . S . Navy . In addition to the necessary offshore defense vessels , other major ships will form aircraft carrier combat groups or amphibious attack groups as needed .
The role of the new frigate in the future aircraft carrier battle group should act as the anti-submarine main force and the mid-to-near area empty position , in the amphibious attack ship strike group should act as the frigate type , then according to this demand the new frigate must have the strong anti-submarine ability and the good mid-range area empty ability .
Based on the above-mentioned positioning , we can boldly imagine the general appearance of the future domestic frigate .
First of all , there will be a significant increase in displacement relative to the current model 054A frigate . It is estimated that the displacement of the new frigate will reach about 5,000 - 6,000 tons . The power system will adopt an integrated power propulsion system consisting of a QC 280 modified gas turbine and two diesel engines , with a maximum speed expected to reach about 30 knots and a substantial increase in endurance ; As for the weapon configuration 76 mm main gun and 1130 near anti-aircraft gun should be retained , but a red flag 10 launch system will be added . Behind the main gun there should be a 32 - 48 unit red flag 16 modified and fish-8 common vertical hair system , which should be installed in the rear of the hull with an 8 - 16 unit large vertical hair system for the launch of eagles and new cruise missiles ; and if the main gun is equipped with a low-level radar system , it should also be used for the development of two-level radar systems .
As a result , the overall level of the new frigate will reach the top level in the world , even when compared with the FFG in the US .
Of course , the above-mentioned concept is only the author's guess on the domestic new frigate , the concrete how we can only wait until the launch of the new frigate , let us look forward to it .
