China's self-driving tourism market size or more than 10 billion yuan in 2020
[ Abstract ] In the context of rising consumption and the prevalence of free travel , self-driving is encouraged by national policies and loved by more and more consumers .
But at the same time , the self-driving market , which is expected to break through the trillion-dollar scale , is also facing double challenges .
In the context of consumer escalation and the prevalence of free travel , self-driving is encouraged by national policies and favored by more and more consumers .
On the one hand , the development of the self-driving industry is not directly proportional to the market demand . On the other hand , the self-driving organizers , such as self-driving clubs and travel agencies , are facing a meagre profit dilemma . On the other hand , the infrastructure and services facing self-driving travel are still in the primary stage .
60 % of the total number of domestic visitors , the size of the market is expected to exceed 10 billion
In 2016 , the total number of domestic tourists was 4.44 billion , with self-driving accounting for about 60 % of the total number of domestic tourists , and the scale of the self-driving market is expected to exceed 10 billion by 2020 .
According to statistics from the China Travel and Transportation Association on the number of people traveling by car , the number of people traveling by car has continued to increase in the past five years , accounting for more than half of the total number of people traveling in China .
At the same time , more attention and support has been shown at the regional and national levels to the emerging field of self-driving . From 2016 to 2017 , policies and regulations related to self-driving , passenger cars and camping tourism have been introduced intensively .
In July 2017 , the National Tourism Administration , the State General Administration of Sports and other eight departments jointly promulgated the " Plan for the Development of Automotive Self-driving Sports Camp " ; in the same month , the Development and Reform Commission , the Ministry of Finance and other 14 departments jointly issued the Action Plan for Promoting Quality Upgrading of Rural Tourism Development ( 2017 ) , self-driving tours were highlighted .
The introduction of the policy provides opportunities and policy guidance for the development of domestic self-driving tourism .
Self-driving tour club profit is meager , complete industrial chain is the key
Although the domestic self-driving market potential is huge , the national policy is actively guided , but the self-driving industry is still in the primary stage .
According to the China Annual Development Report 2016 - 2017 , there are thousands of self-driving clubs , car clubs and car clubs in China , but the proportion of tourists who arrange their own travel by themselves accounts for the majority , with only about 15 percent of the total number of visitors participating in auto-driving clubs , self-driving clubs and other organizations .
At the same time , there are only a few online travel enterprises and traditional travel agencies that develop their own self-driving products . Many online travel platforms sell only self-driving products provided by some suppliers , and some self-driving clubs are also important suppliers .
From the organization of self-driving activities , covered " eat , live , travel , travel , purchase , entertainment " many aspects , high degree of fragmentation , upstream supply chain heavy , tourists consumption randomness .
Li Guanjie , founder and CEO of the Beijing World Auto Club , believes that the self-driving club is essentially similar to the travel agency . In the early days , the main profit model was based on off-line activities , and the core point is the self-driving line products and tour leader services .
But now in the field of self-driving tour line product homogenization is serious , the tour leader service level is uneven , the self-driving tour club is facing the need of re-transformation .
It can be seen that the self-driving tour itself is not an independent industry , but with its self-driving displacement characteristics to form a cross-region , industry ecological circle , forming a complete industrial chain is very important .
Experts point out that in addition to basic tourism consumption , experience is a more important consumption element .
Therefore , for the development of self-driving industry , we should enhance the experience characteristics , develop the " self-driving + " theme and the IP of self-driving products .
Scenic roads are not only roads , but car camps should not only meet food and lodging
In the face of the rise of self-driving travel , the basic supporting development of self-driving travel is also relatively primary .
Li Guanjie pointed out that the tourist scenic road is not just a road , but the elements of transportation and tourism need to be integrated into it , but the road repair and tourism itself are responsible for the two departments , the transport sector to increase the tourism elements , but also stay in the construction of toilet , consultation center , propaganda column and other facilities , and the integration of tourism is not high .
Compared with the well-known self-driving route " United States 66 Highway " , the construction experience is worth reference .
The scenic route design is no longer the most direct and fast route between the point of departure and the destination , but follows the design concept of " experience driving fun " to provide the best enjoyment for self-driving visitors to enjoy the beautiful scenery along the road . The scenic route can link the point-shaped and face-shaped tourism landscape , preserving the historical value and cultural value of the eco-tourism resources along the route , as well as organizing various thematic activities to enhance the participation and recreation experience of tourists and create economic benefits for local tourism .
In addition to the scenic road , the camp is also an important supporting facility for self-driving tour .
But the new Beijing News reporter knows that among the self-driving tourists , there are not many consumers who choose to stay in the camp .
In their view , many camps tend to be infrastructure-oriented and can only meet the needs of food and shelter , low-grade , single-product , and self-driving , which contains a lot of elements .
Some people in the industry who do not want to be named said that in the past few years , many of the enterprises that do camp are to take the land , take the land , the later supporting infrastructure construction and services have not kept up , operating conditions are a lot of losses , and there is no late capital injection , it is difficult to do some corresponding supporting products .
Consumers
According to data released by the China Travel and Transportation Association in 2017 , self-driving groups are concentrated at 21 - 40 years of age , especially at 31 - 40 years of age , which has a certain economic base and a high demand for personalized tourism , and are mostly parent-child tourists .
From the accommodation survey , self-driving people prefer non-standard accommodation .
From the type of self-driving tour , peripheral self-driving is the main type of self-driving , accounting for 84.32 % .
Outbound self-driving is the yearning of many people , but the ratio is still smaller .
At the same time , with the increase in consumer demand , tourists who used to like to drive " tourist attractions " began to change their minds , instead of " get off the bus to take photos , get on the train to sleep " , but pay more attention to the experience and process of the journey .
Rokid , an intelligent interactive robot developer , gets new investment in Temasek
In recent years , start-ups in the field of artificial intelligence have continued to enjoy a capital boom .
Artificial Intelligence Rokid recently completed a new round of financing , led by Temasek , Credit Suisse , CDIB ( the investment arm of Taiwan's China Development Finance Holdings ) , and old shareholder IDG capital .
It is reported that this round of financing of about $ 100 million , Credit Suisse and CDIB for the first time in the domestic artificial intelligence financing transactions .
Rokid is an intelligent interactive robot developer , dedicated to robotics research , products can control home intelligent equipment , can continue to learn and grow independently , and also has the functions of recognition , understanding , feedback and so on .
This round of financing will be mainly used for research and development , talent introduction , strategic promotion and industrial chain investment layout .
Earlier , in August 2014 , Rokid received IDG , linear capital , Mfund , Yuan Jing capital of US $ 8.3 million Angel Wheel Investment . In October 2015 , the company also received Wadden International Investment , Angel Investor with the investment of US $ 10 million A Wheel Investment ; On November 1 , 2016 , Rokid completed the investment of IDG , IDG , Mfund , and other international financing institutions .
At the time , Rokid said , B-round financing after the company's valuation has reached $ 450 million .
In May 2017 , Rokid released the consumer-level intelligent voice robot " Ruki Moonstone " , which combines artificial intelligence with family scenes at a price of 1,399 yuan .
The robot uses speech synthesis , natural language understanding , speech recognition and microphone array technology , with chat dialogue , playing music , intelligent home functions .
Has won two awards at the International Consumer Electronics Fair ( CES ) Tech For A Better World and Home Audio / Video Competitions , as well as the German IF Design Award , which is known as the Oscar for the design industry .
On the just-closed 2018 CES , Rokid released a new product : consumer-level enhanced reality AR glasses Rokid Glass .
The glasses will be used as a stand-alone headset , with no need to connect to smartphones or external computers , and are expected to be commercialized by 2018 .
Earlier , the company has released first-generation home robot Rokid Alien and second-generation product intelligent speaker Rokid Pebble .
