China's space science satellite series of the first star , but also the world's first dark matter particle detection satellite Wukong
Over the past two years in orbit , four scans of the full-day area have detected more than 3.5 billion high-energy particles , the most accurate in the world
The results were published in the international academic journal Nature
In space , we have observed a new one that has not been observed before , one that cannot be explained or explained by the theory that has been used
The significance of this research is multiple , and most importantly , it shows that Chinese scientists are using the most cutting-edge technology
The ability to manufacture scientific instruments to detect a very difficult scientific problem .
